2.40pm It's tea and how the session and the Test has turned. Bilal Asif, aged 33, has impressed in his very first outing as a Test cricket, an opportunity that appeared to have bypassed him when he was branded 'ordinary' last year. He's scythed through Australia's top order once the 142-run opening stand between Finch and Khawaja was dismantled by Mohammad Abbas. Australia lost 4 for 11 and the ghosts that didn't exist till even a couple of hours ago are suddenly lurking from all corners, teasing and tormenting Australia just the way they didn't want to be. Time for Tim Paine to play a captain's knock here along with one of his deputies. Can they steer Australia past the follow-on mark? Alex Malcolm will be here in 20 minutes to tell you.
